'''Duan Tianjie''' ({{zh|s=段天杰|t=|p=Duàn Tiānjié}}) is a [[major general]] in the [[People's Liberation Army]] (PLA). He was placed under investigation by PLA's [[Central Commission for Discipline Inspection|anti-corruption agency]] in November 2014 and transferred to the military judicial organ in January 2015.<ref>{{cite news|title=14 generals named in corruption crackdown|url=http://www.shanghaidaily.com/national/flies-and-tigers/14-generals-named-in-corruption-crackdown/shdaily.shtml|work=Shanghaidaily|date=2015-03-03}}</ref> Previously he served as Deputy Director of the Political Department of [[PLA National Defence University]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Details about high level of corruption in China's PLA revealed (Re-issuing for all needing)|url=https://in.news.yahoo.com/details-high-level-corruption-chinas-pla-revealed-issuing-060355352.html|work=Yahoo|date=2015-05-27}}</ref>
Duan Tianjie was also a [[columnist]] in ''Liberation Army Daily'' ({{zh | t=| s=《解放军报》| hp=|labels=no}}), and he once served as president of ''Zhanyou Bao'' ({{zh | t=| s=《战友报》| hp=|labels=no}}).<ref>{{cite news|author= |url=http://news.163.com/15/0302/19/AJNP7KCA00014SEH.html |script-title=zh:国防大学政治部副主任段天杰落马，曾自诩“军人中的文人” |newspaper=163.COM |date= 2015-03-02|language=zh |location=}}</ref>
